1
00:00:23,123 --> 00:00:26,126
<i>(Thinking)</i>
<i>Sometimes I forget I'm still</i>
<i>just a kid...</i>

2
00:00:28,361 --> 00:00:31,965
[panting breaths]

3
00:00:46,446 --> 00:00:50,517
<i>...I still have years to go</i>
<i>before I'm all grown up...</i>

4
00:00:50,517 --> 00:00:55,188
Oooh, la la! Keep
that kiss going! Bonus
points for duration!

5
00:00:58,324 --> 00:01:01,467
<i>(Thinking)</i>
<i>I wonder how Pegasus sees me?</i>

6
00:01:01,502 --> 00:01:04,204
<i>Am I just a kid to him, too?</i>

7
00:01:05,706 --> 00:01:07,741
Hm?

8
00:01:07,808 --> 00:01:09,042
[grouchy groan]

9
00:01:09,075 --> 00:01:10,711
What is it?

10
00:01:10,744 --> 00:01:14,748
It's hard to believe that
technically you're more of
an adult than I am.

11
00:01:14,815 --> 00:01:16,917
Eh? Whatta you mean,
“technically? ”

12
00:01:16,983 --> 00:01:18,652
And you should
do your homework!

13
00:01:18,685 --> 00:01:20,486
I've finished <i>mine.</i>

14
00:01:20,521 --> 00:01:24,658
[groan] Well, of course you
have, 'cuz your homework's easy.

15
00:01:24,691 --> 00:01:26,660
[chewing]

16
00:01:26,693 --> 00:01:32,065
[sigh] I wish I could go back to
being a little kid, when all the
math problems were a piece of
cake!

17
00:01:34,501 --> 00:01:36,537
Hey, where do you
think you're going?

18
00:01:36,570 --> 00:01:38,171
Outside.

19
00:01:38,204 --> 00:01:41,041
Oh! Great idea! I'll come with
you to make sure you don't get
into any trouble!

20
00:01:41,074 --> 00:01:45,078
<i>(Chibi‐Usa)</i>
<i>I'll be fine. Besides, you</i>
<i>haven't finished your homework.</i>

21
00:01:45,078 --> 00:01:48,582
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>It can wait. I'm your guardian,</i>
<i>I have to look after you.</i>

22
00:01:48,582 --> 00:01:51,284
<i>(Chibi‐Usa)</i>
<i>Yeah? Well sometimes I feel</i>
<i>like I'm your guardian&</i>

23
00:01:51,351 --> 00:01:53,554
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Huh? Did you say something?</i>

24
00:01:55,455 --> 00:02:05,539
♪

25
00:02:05,539 --> 00:02:25,626
♪

26
00:02:25,626 --> 00:02:45,646
♪

27
00:02:45,646 --> 00:03:05,672
♪

28
00:03:05,672 --> 00:03:25,526
♪

29
00:03:31,031 --> 00:03:36,570
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Pegasus's Secret: The Boy Who</i>
<i>Protects the Dream World</i>

30
00:03:41,174 --> 00:03:46,046
<i>(Palla‐Palla)</i>
<i>And so, the brave prince came</i>
<i>riding to her rescue on his</i>
<i>white horse!</i>

31
00:03:46,079 --> 00:03:50,551
<i>But then‐‐!... he got killed by</i>
<i>the sorcerer living in the</i>
<i>woods...</i>

32
00:03:50,584 --> 00:03:53,520
<i>...and then the princess</i>
<i>got killed, too.</i>

33
00:03:53,554 --> 00:03:56,923
<i>And then the sorcerer</i>
<i>died...just because.</i>

34
00:03:56,990 --> 00:03:59,926
And so everyone died
happily ever after!

35
00:03:59,993 --> 00:04:01,367
You're kidding.

36
00:04:01,401 --> 00:04:03,069
That ending came
out of nowhere.

37
00:04:03,103 --> 00:04:05,739
<i>(girl)</i>
<i>Yeah. Don't you know anything</i>
<i>about foreshadowing?</i>

38
00:04:05,772 --> 00:04:08,742
<i>(girl)</i>
<i>You know, It kinda dragged</i>
<i>in the middle, too.</i>

39
00:04:08,742 --> 00:04:11,545
You are all so annoying!

40
00:04:11,578 --> 00:04:14,414
Ooh, look! A tree made of candy!

41
00:04:14,447 --> 00:04:18,184
Palla‐Palla's gonna speed this
up and do all of you at once!...

42
00:04:18,218 --> 00:04:20,086
Orb Shot!

43
00:04:21,755 --> 00:04:24,090
[screams]

44
00:04:24,124 --> 00:04:28,128
Pretty neat, isn't it? It's
called the Shotgun Special!

45
00:04:28,629 --> 00:04:30,196
<i>(Sailor Moon)</i>
<i>What do you think you're doing?</i>

46
00:04:30,230 --> 00:04:31,698
Huh?

47
00:04:31,732 --> 00:04:34,701
How dare you meddle with
children who haven't even
finished their homework!

48
00:04:34,734 --> 00:04:36,603
Hey, sounds like
someone I know.

49
00:04:36,636 --> 00:04:38,538
Never mind that now,
just finish the speech!

50
00:04:38,572 --> 00:04:42,543
Oh, uh‐‐ We won't forgive you
for trying to shatter their
dreams!

51
00:04:42,576 --> 00:04:43,877
We're the Pretty Guardians...

52
00:04:43,910 --> 00:04:49,115
......who fight for
love and for justice!

53
00:04:49,149 --> 00:04:51,952
I am Sailor Moon!

54
00:04:51,985 --> 00:04:55,488
And I am Sailor Chibi Moon!

55
00:04:55,556 --> 00:04:57,824
And in the name of the Moon...

56
00:04:57,891 --> 00:04:59,626
‐...we'll punish you!
‐...we'll punish you!

57
00:04:59,660 --> 00:05:01,968
Not you two again!

58
00:05:01,968 --> 00:05:05,071
<i>It was already a bad day! All</i>
<i>the Dream Mirrors were blanks!</i>

59
00:05:05,105 --> 00:05:06,607
[groans]

60
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:09,475
<i>(Palla‐Palla)</i>
<i>Why do you care so much about</i>
<i>their dreams, anyway?</i>

61
00:05:09,510 --> 00:05:11,244
Are they really all
that important?

62
00:05:11,277 --> 00:05:12,312
Of course they are!

63
00:05:12,345 --> 00:05:14,147
Most definitely!

64
00:05:14,147 --> 00:05:17,918
But when you dream about doing
something or getting something
or becoming something you're

65
00:05:17,951 --> 00:05:20,420
not, isn't that what people
call being selfish?

66
00:05:20,453 --> 00:05:21,788
Huh!?

67
00:05:21,822 --> 00:05:23,423
Selfish, you say?

68
00:05:23,456 --> 00:05:25,258
...Is it?

69
00:05:25,291 --> 00:05:27,493
Hmmm..

70
00:05:27,528 --> 00:05:33,099
Well, wishing you could be a
little kid again just because
your math homework would be
easier, that's selfish.

71
00:05:33,133 --> 00:05:35,669
But dreaming of being a
grownup, that's more like‐‐

72
00:05:35,669 --> 00:05:40,273
Whoa, now that is selfish.
Ooh! Ssssssuper‐duper selfish!

73
00:05:40,306 --> 00:05:41,508
[groans]

74
00:05:41,508 --> 00:05:42,375
<i>(Chibi Moon)</i>
<i>And why is that?!</i>

75
00:05:42,442 --> 00:05:44,010
<i>(Sailor Moon)</i>
<i>Because it just is!</i>

76
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:46,312
<i>(Chibi Moon)</i>
<i>I'm going to be an adult, but</i>
<i>you'll never be a kid again!</i>

77
00:05:46,346 --> 00:05:47,681
<i>(Sailor Moon)</i>
<i>That's why it's called a dream!</i>

78
00:05:47,681 --> 00:05:48,682
<i>(Chibi Moon)</i>
<i>And it's selfish!</i>

79
00:05:48,715 --> 00:05:50,150
<i>(Sailor Moon)</i>
<i>Why is that being selfish??</i>

80
00:05:50,183 --> 00:05:51,184
<i>(Chibi Moon)</i>
<i>Because it just is!</i>

81
00:05:51,184 --> 00:05:52,352
<i>(Sailor Moon)</i>
<i>That doesn't make any sense!</i>

82
00:05:52,352 --> 00:05:54,120
Opposite Orb!

83
00:05:57,157 --> 00:06:08,174
[arguing]

84
00:06:08,208 --> 00:06:10,076
‐Huh?
‐Huh?

85
00:06:12,478 --> 00:06:15,882
Palla‐Palla just made your
dreams come true! Isn't she
nice?

86
00:06:15,882 --> 00:06:17,918
There's nothing
“nice ” about you!

87
00:06:17,984 --> 00:06:22,022
Go on, Chibi Moon,
use your Carillon!

88
00:06:22,055 --> 00:06:24,424
Summon Pegasu‐‐
Uh, Chibi Moon?

89
00:06:31,397 --> 00:06:33,567
<i>(Thinking)</i>
<i>My body's all grown up...</i>

90
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:38,104
[happy sigh]

91
00:06:38,171 --> 00:06:39,506
Come on, Chibi Moon!

92
00:06:39,540 --> 00:06:40,574
Huh?

93
00:06:40,574 --> 00:06:42,242
Use the Carillon!

94
00:06:42,275 --> 00:06:43,910
Hm!

95
00:06:43,944 --> 00:06:48,615
Please, Pegasus! Protect
everyone's dream!

96
00:06:49,049 --> 00:06:52,586
<i>(Thinking)</i>
<i>I wonder how Pegasus will</i>
<i>react when he sees me.</i>

97
00:06:52,586 --> 00:06:56,957
Twinkle Yell!

98
00:06:58,859 --> 00:07:01,401
[gasp]

99
00:07:01,434 --> 00:07:02,402
[gasp]

100
00:07:02,435 --> 00:07:04,104
What is it?
What's wrong?!

101
00:07:04,137 --> 00:07:06,306
It's not working...

102
00:07:06,372 --> 00:07:09,776
[giggle] You can't summon
Pegasus, can you?

103
00:07:09,810 --> 00:07:11,277
[angry grunts]

104
00:07:19,285 --> 00:07:21,154
[screams]
What are those!?

105
00:07:21,287 --> 00:07:23,489
Never mind, run!

106
00:07:24,157 --> 00:07:27,060
[giggle] This is fun!

107
00:07:27,093 --> 00:07:28,562
<i>(Sailor Mercury)</i>
<i>Hold it right there!</i>

108
00:07:28,595 --> 00:07:31,131
<i>(Sailor Mars)</i>
<i>How dare you stir up trouble</i>
<i>on such a beautiful day!</i>

109
00:07:31,131 --> 00:07:33,634
Not that there's ever
a good time for it!

110
00:07:33,634 --> 00:07:36,970
You'll have to deal with us now
and that won't be so much fun.

111
00:07:37,003 --> 00:07:40,807
Guess it's time to go. Oh,
well! Maybe next time...

112
00:07:40,807 --> 00:07:41,908
Bye!

113
00:07:41,942 --> 00:07:43,343
Huh?

114
00:07:44,477 --> 00:07:47,514
[exhausted sighs]

115
00:07:48,348 --> 00:07:49,415
You two all right?

116
00:07:49,449 --> 00:07:50,283
Wait...

117
00:07:50,316 --> 00:07:51,417
Hold on...

118
00:07:51,451 --> 00:07:56,122
there's something...

119
00:07:56,156 --> 00:07:58,124
(all)
...definitely odd here..!

120
00:08:00,834 --> 00:08:03,970
[small groan]

121
00:08:06,773 --> 00:08:13,514
<i>(Thinking)</i>
<i>It's still here... I was worried</i>
<i>it might have disappeared</i>
<i>again...</i>

122
00:08:13,980 --> 00:08:16,517
<i>But why didn't he</i>
<i>come when I called?</i>

123
00:08:22,188 --> 00:08:24,157
Pegasus...!

124
00:08:25,358 --> 00:08:27,861
Pegasus, come out!

125
00:08:29,630 --> 00:08:32,165
Where are you!?

126
00:08:33,800 --> 00:08:34,801
Please come...

127
00:08:34,835 --> 00:08:38,872
Talk to me, Pegasus...

128
00:08:39,706 --> 00:08:42,876
Say something...! [sob]

129
00:08:47,213 --> 00:08:50,517
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Anyway, I told my parents we're</i>
<i>spending the night at Rei's</i>
<i>place,</i>

130
00:08:50,551 --> 00:08:52,385
<i>but really we want</i>
<i>to stay at your place!</i>

131
00:08:52,385 --> 00:08:54,487
So, can we?

132
00:08:54,521 --> 00:08:55,689
[giggle]

133
00:08:55,722 --> 00:08:58,825
I get it... I'm
being punk'd, right?

134
00:08:58,859 --> 00:09:01,067
No, you're not.

135
00:09:02,903 --> 00:09:06,573
You only get to enjoy this sort
of privilege when you're a kid.

136
00:09:06,573 --> 00:09:11,077
Chibi‐Usa, go on and get to bed,
before you catch a cold.

137
00:09:11,111 --> 00:09:12,613
Okay.

138
00:09:14,581 --> 00:09:18,552
<i>(Thinking)</i>
<i>I've always yearned for the day</i>
<i>I'd have long arms and</i>
<i>legs...and a puffy chest.</i>

139
00:09:18,585 --> 00:09:22,556
I'm not a little girl anymore.

140
00:09:22,589 --> 00:09:27,393
But I wanted...
Pegasus to see me.

141
00:09:29,930 --> 00:09:32,799
[snoring]

142
00:09:32,866 --> 00:09:35,268
<i>(Pegasus)</i>
<i>Young Maiden...</i>

143
00:09:36,269 --> 00:09:38,872
<i>(Pegasus)</i>
<i>Young maiden...!</i>

144
00:09:38,905 --> 00:09:40,774
Pegasus!

145
00:09:49,883 --> 00:09:57,958
[panting]

146
00:10:01,835 --> 00:10:04,738
[gasps]

147
00:10:04,738 --> 00:10:09,009
Pegasus!

148
00:10:10,410 --> 00:10:11,845
[neighs]

149
00:10:13,013 --> 00:10:14,915
[happy gasp]

150
00:10:17,518 --> 00:10:20,754
Do you know where I
can find Pegasus?

151
00:10:21,855 --> 00:10:23,757
[gasp]

152
00:10:27,427 --> 00:10:30,096
[frightened gasp]

153
00:10:30,130 --> 00:10:31,565
<i>(Pegasus)</i>
<i>My little maiden...</i>

154
00:10:31,598 --> 00:10:33,900
Huh?

155
00:10:43,376 --> 00:10:46,312
[gasp]

156
00:10:52,485 --> 00:10:55,221
[happy neigh]

157
00:11:00,934 --> 00:11:03,637
Pegasus...!

158
00:11:06,239 --> 00:11:14,515
<i>♪ Sailor Moon</i>

159
00:11:18,151 --> 00:11:27,828
<i>♪ Sailor Moon</i>

160
00:11:28,629 --> 00:11:30,997
I thought I'd never
see you again.

161
00:11:31,031 --> 00:11:33,967
Yes... I lost sight
of where you were.

162
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:35,769
Huh?

163
00:11:35,802 --> 00:11:40,206
The light of your dreams
was no longer reaching me.

164
00:11:40,206 --> 00:11:43,644
I... I don't
understand, Pegasus.

165
00:11:43,677 --> 00:11:46,880
You are inside the Dream World.

166
00:11:49,983 --> 00:11:51,952
[gasps]

167
00:12:04,170 --> 00:12:06,372
The Dream World...

168
00:12:18,084 --> 00:12:19,720
What's that?

169
00:12:20,220 --> 00:12:23,924
The world where my
people live. Elysion.

170
00:12:23,924 --> 00:12:26,560
That's the world where you live?

171
00:12:26,593 --> 00:12:29,229
I'd like to see it.

172
00:12:31,932 --> 00:12:34,535
Then let us go.

173
00:12:34,568 --> 00:12:36,503
[gasp]

174
00:12:36,537 --> 00:12:38,438
Climb onto my back.

175
00:12:39,606 --> 00:12:41,608
Okay...

176
00:12:42,709 --> 00:12:45,345
Too heavy?

177
00:12:45,378 --> 00:12:47,948
Not at all. Hang
on tight now.

178
00:12:48,114 --> 00:12:49,449
Okay!

179
00:13:08,108 --> 00:13:11,377
[gasps]

180
00:13:12,779 --> 00:13:14,915
[happy sigh]

181
00:13:19,052 --> 00:13:21,154
This ...is your wor?

182
00:13:21,221 --> 00:13:24,290
Yes. Elysion...

183
00:13:24,324 --> 00:13:31,765
Once, it was supported by the
beautiful dreams of the people
of Earth... But then...

184
00:13:31,798 --> 00:13:39,072
One day, without warning, they
came...beings who were after the
Golden Crystal.

185
00:13:39,105 --> 00:13:41,908
The Golden Crystal?

186
00:13:41,942 --> 00:13:47,180
<i>They come from the chaos and</i>
<i>darkness of the New Moon...</i>

187
00:13:47,247 --> 00:13:50,016
<i>They're known as the Dead Moon.</i>

188
00:14:03,604 --> 00:14:06,306
<i>If the Golden Crystal falls</i>
<i>into their hands,</i>

189
00:14:06,339 --> 00:14:13,514
<i>then not only Elysion, but the</i>
<i>Earth, too, will be transformed</i>
<i>into a world of darkness.</i>

190
00:14:13,547 --> 00:14:17,718
<i>Therefore, they must never gain</i>
<i>possession of the Golden</i>
<i>Crystal.</i>

191
00:14:20,887 --> 00:14:25,726
They nearly did, once, after I
became their prisoner...

192
00:14:25,792 --> 00:14:36,002
<i>(Queen Nehalennia)</i>
<i>[evil laugh] The Golden Crystal</i>
<i>belongs to me now...</i>

193
00:14:36,036 --> 00:14:44,077
<i>As do Elysion and Earth. They</i>
<i>are all mine!... [evil laugh]</i>

194
00:14:51,518 --> 00:14:57,057
<i>(Pegasus)</i>
<i>It was then that I saw a</i>
<i>light... A light made of</i>
<i>beautiful dreams...</i>

195
00:14:57,090 --> 00:14:59,726
<i>The last light for me</i>
<i>to cling to.</i>

196
00:15:01,061 --> 00:15:07,240
<i>Drawn by that light, I</i>
<i>transformed myself into</i>
<i>Pegasus...and headed toward it.</i>

197
00:15:13,446 --> 00:15:16,449
<i>And then I met you...</i>

198
00:15:16,950 --> 00:15:22,789
<i>a person who shined</i>
<i>brilliantly...like a beautiful</i>
<i>dream crystal.</i>

199
00:15:24,057 --> 00:15:25,959
[gasp]

200
00:15:26,026 --> 00:15:30,063
But now, I can no
longer see that light.

201
00:15:30,096 --> 00:15:31,464
[gasp]

202
00:15:33,233 --> 00:15:36,136
<i>(Pegasus)</i>
<i>The New Moon's magic has</i>
<i>fulfilled your dream of</i>
<i>becoming an adult...</i>

203
00:15:36,202 --> 00:15:44,310
<i>But at the same time, that magic</i>
<i>of the New Moon has cast shadow</i>
<i>over your true dream.</i>

204
00:15:44,310 --> 00:15:47,814
My true dream, Pegasus?

205
00:15:47,814 --> 00:15:53,086
You must get it back, the light
of your true dream...

206
00:15:53,119 --> 00:15:57,558
If you don't, I will never again
be able to find you.

207
00:15:57,924 --> 00:16:04,337
[gasp] What do you mean‐‐?...Are
you telling me I'll never be
able to see you anymore?

208
00:16:04,671 --> 00:16:10,443
No...! No, that
can't happen...

209
00:16:11,011 --> 00:16:13,179
I don't want that..!

210
00:16:15,415 --> 00:16:19,085
No, Pegasus...

211
00:16:19,119 --> 00:16:25,992
No, no! No! No‐‐!

212
00:16:45,445 --> 00:16:51,685
[gasp] It's too big.

213
00:16:55,689 --> 00:16:58,158
[happy sigh]

214
00:17:00,060 --> 00:17:04,805
Young maiden... we need the
light of your beautiful dream.

215
00:17:21,054 --> 00:17:22,589
[gasp]

216
00:17:24,691 --> 00:17:30,764
From Elysion, I watch over the
many dreams of the people of
Earth and I stand guard over the
Golden Crystal.

217
00:17:30,831 --> 00:17:34,100
I am called...Helios.

218
00:17:35,602 --> 00:17:37,270
Helios..?

219
00:17:37,337 --> 00:17:39,239
[gasp]

220
00:17:39,272 --> 00:17:40,607
Was it a dream?

221
00:17:40,674 --> 00:17:43,577
Stop it, Rei! You're choking
me to death, cut it out!

222
00:17:43,610 --> 00:17:46,379
I'm back to normal again...

223
00:17:46,412 --> 00:17:51,217
<i>[distant sounds]</i>

224
00:17:51,251 --> 00:17:55,756
<i>(Palla‐Palla)</i>
<i>Oh, Golden Mirror, Golden</i>
<i>Mirror, where are you‐hooo?</i>

225
00:17:55,789 --> 00:18:01,467
You're kidding, all these
mirrors and not one of
them's a golden one?...

226
00:18:01,467 --> 00:18:03,103
<i>(Sailor Guardians)</i>
<i>Hold it right there!</i>

227
00:18:03,136 --> 00:18:07,473
You toyed with the heart
of a girl who hates
doing her homework!

228
00:18:07,473 --> 00:18:11,044
And you toyed with the heart of
a girl who dreams of growing up!

229
00:18:11,077 --> 00:18:14,147
Not to mention toying with the
dreams of all these children!

230
00:18:14,214 --> 00:18:16,449
And stirring up trouble in
the middle of the night!

231
00:18:16,482 --> 00:18:18,619
You're in need of
serious disciplining!

232
00:18:18,652 --> 00:18:21,955
The Sailor Guardians will not
let you get away with this!

233
00:18:21,988 --> 00:18:23,990
In the name of the Moon...

234
00:18:24,057 --> 00:18:25,992
‐...we'll punish you!
‐...we'll punish you!

235
00:18:26,059 --> 00:18:28,394
Wait, how come you two
are back to normal?

236
00:18:28,428 --> 00:18:35,135
Ha! Oh well, whatever. Come
forth, Palla‐Palla's Lemures,
Pero‐Pero, the Candy Doll!

237
00:18:35,168 --> 00:18:41,241
Candy!!

238
00:18:42,509 --> 00:18:44,477
I'm Pero‐Pero!

239
00:18:44,511 --> 00:18:46,613
Show 'em a good time, okay?

240
00:18:46,647 --> 00:18:47,781
Okey‐dokey!

241
00:18:47,814 --> 00:18:50,684
I bet you kids
would like some candy.

242
00:18:50,684 --> 00:18:53,687
Everyone loves candy!!

243
00:18:53,687 --> 00:18:56,422
Jupiter... Oak Evolution!

244
00:19:02,769 --> 00:19:06,139
Pero pero pero pero pero!

245
00:19:06,172 --> 00:19:08,542
Oh, eww! They multiplied!!

246
00:19:08,609 --> 00:19:17,450
Venus ...Love and Beauty Shock!

247
00:19:18,051 --> 00:19:20,386
Pero pero pero pero pero !!

248
00:19:20,453 --> 00:19:21,988
Yep, they multiplied again.

249
00:19:22,022 --> 00:19:23,389
...Again!?

250
00:19:23,389 --> 00:19:29,395
Mars...Flame Sniper!

251
00:19:31,331 --> 00:19:35,869
Pero pero pero pero pero !!

252
00:19:35,902 --> 00:19:37,804
Guess that made 'em
multiply, too!

253
00:19:37,838 --> 00:19:40,240
And now they're a big,
gross, gloppy mess!

254
00:19:40,240 --> 00:19:46,680
Mercury...Aqua Rhapsody!

255
00:19:48,849 --> 00:19:52,152
Pero pero pero pe‐‐

256
00:19:53,253 --> 00:19:55,756
[cheering]

257
00:19:55,822 --> 00:19:59,059
Well, I guess you guys
didn't like my candy!

258
00:19:59,092 --> 00:20:04,805
How about this tasty treat?

259
00:20:06,039 --> 00:20:07,641
Argh!

260
00:20:07,674 --> 00:20:12,378
It's wrong for children to be
given treats before a hearty
and nutritious meal!

261
00:20:12,445 --> 00:20:14,948
Huh!?

262
00:20:14,981 --> 00:20:19,853
Now Sailor Moo‐‐ I said,
Now Sailor Moon!

263
00:20:19,886 --> 00:20:21,888
Coming...!

264
00:20:21,955 --> 00:20:26,960
Please, Pegasus! Protect
everyone's dream!

265
00:20:28,562 --> 00:20:30,163
<i>(Thinking)</i>
<i>Pegasus...</i>

266
00:20:30,196 --> 00:20:32,799
Twinkle Yell!

267
00:20:38,672 --> 00:20:40,406
[neigh]

268
00:20:54,755 --> 00:21:01,267
Moon Gorgeous Meditation!

269
00:21:12,879 --> 00:21:18,284
Parting is such sweet
sorrow!... Stage Out!

270
00:21:29,730 --> 00:21:31,297
It's Pegasus.

271
00:21:31,297 --> 00:21:32,933
He's lovely.

272
00:21:32,966 --> 00:21:35,802
[amazed gasps]

273
00:21:35,869 --> 00:21:39,139
It's almost like he's looking
at you, Chibi Moon.

274
00:21:39,139 --> 00:21:41,908
<i>(Chibi Moon)</i>
<i>[sigh]</i>

275
00:21:43,309 --> 00:21:46,146
<i>(Sailor Jupiter)</i>
<i>By the way, how did you</i>
<i>turn back to normal?</i>

276
00:21:46,146 --> 00:21:48,615
Huh? Oh, it happened
while we were asleep.

277
00:21:48,649 --> 00:21:51,484
<i>(Sailor Mercury)</i>
<i>Too bad. I thought you were</i>
<i>cute as little Sailor Moon.</i>

278
00:21:51,552 --> 00:21:53,820
<i>(Sailor Moon)</i>
<i>Get outta here! [giggle]</i>

279
00:21:55,255 --> 00:21:59,793
<i>(Thinking)</i>
<i>Pegasus, I think I know</i>
<i>you a little better now...</i>

280
00:21:59,826 --> 00:22:04,070
<i>..But... was</i>
<i>it all just a dream?</i>

281
00:22:04,104 --> 00:22:07,473
<i>Even&that kiss?</i>

282
00:22:07,508 --> 00:22:12,112
<i>...Tell me... Pegasus.</i>

283
00:22:19,620 --> 00:22:29,696
♪

284
00:22:29,696 --> 00:22:49,716
♪

285
00:22:49,716 --> 00:23:09,743
♪

286
00:23:09,743 --> 00:23:29,863
♪

287
00:23:29,863 --> 00:23:48,849
♪

288
00:23:53,019 --> 00:23:56,456
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Mamo, I think Chibi‐Usa's</i>
<i>found a boy she likes.</i>

289
00:23:56,523 --> 00:23:58,258
<i>(Mamoru)</i>
<i>Really? What do you</i>
<i>know about him?</i>

290
00:23:58,291 --> 00:24:00,293
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Well, he dresses all</i>
<i>in white, and‐‐</i>

291
00:24:00,360 --> 00:24:02,262
<i>(Mamoru)</i>
<i>White?? Unacceptable!</i>

292
00:24:02,295 --> 00:24:06,372
<i>(Mamoru)</i>
<i>Chibi‐Usa's boyfriend should</i>
<i>wear a classic black tuxedo</i>
<i>and carry a red rose!</i>

293
00:24:06,406 --> 00:24:07,874
<i>(Mamoru)</i>
<i>Anything else is out</i>
<i>of the question!</i>

294
00:24:07,908 --> 00:24:09,075
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>That's just weird.</i>

295
00:24:09,109 --> 00:24:11,477
<i>(Mamoru)</i>
<i>No, it's‐‐ Wait. You</i>
<i>think that's weird?</i>

296
00:24:11,477 --> 00:24:15,982
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Next time on Sailor Moon SuperS,</i>
<i>"Chibi‐Usa's Little Rhapsody of</i>
<i>Love."</i>

297
00:24:15,982 --> 00:24:18,451
(Usagi)
The moonlight is a
messenger of love.

